President Obama and National Security Advisor Susan Rice met with Syrian Opposition Coalition President Ahmad Jarba and his delegation. They reaffirmed that Bashar al-Assad has no legitimacy to rule Syria and should not be part of its future. Both sides expressed their commitment to a political solution that involves a transition to a new governing authority. President Obama praised the Coalition's leadership and encouraged them to work towards an inclusive government that represents all Syrians. President Jarba thanked the US for its non-lethal assistance and humanitarian aid. The US condemned the Assad regime's targeting of civilians and the denial of food and aid to those under siege. They also discussed the need to counter terrorist groups in Syria. The US emphasized the illegitimacy of the regime's plans to hold elections and expressed support for the moderate opposition and the Syrian people in their efforts to end the conflict and facilitate a political transition.